tem DB)\n  range_min_bytes = 134217728\n  range_max_bytes = 536870912\n\nRANGE meta:\n  gc.ttlseconds   = 3600   (1 hour)\n  num_replicas    = 5\n\nRANGE system:\n  gc.ttlseconds   = 14400  (4 hours)\n  num_replicas    = 5\n\nRANGE liveness:\n  gc.ttlseconds   = 600    (10 minutes)\n  num_replicas    = 5\n\nTABLE system.public.lease:\n  gc.ttlseconds   = 600    (10 minutes)\n\nTABLE system.public.replication_constraint_stats:\n  gc.ttlseconds   = 600    (10 minutes)\n\nTABLE system.public.replication_stats:\n  gc.ttlseconds   = 600    (10 minutes)\n\nTABLE system.public.statement_statistics:\n  gc.ttlseconds   = 3600   (1 hour)\n\nTABLE system.public.transaction_statistics:\n  gc.ttlseconds   = 3600   (1 hour)\n\nTABLE system.public.tenant_usage:\n  gc.ttlseconds   = 7200   (2 hours)\n\nTABLE system.public.span_stats_tenant_boundaries:\n  gc.ttlseconds   = 3600   (1 hour)\n\nTABLE system.public.statement_activity:\n  gc.ttlseconds   = 3600   (1 hour)\n\nTABLE system.public.transaction_activity:\n  gc.ttlseconds   = 3600   (1 hour)\n\nUSER-DEFINED ZONE OVERRIDES (non-system tables):\n\n  TABLE defaultdb.tenant_b.table_c:\n    gc.ttlseconds   = 14400  (4 hours)\n    num_replicas    = 3\n    range_min_bytes = 134217728\n    range_max_bytes = 536870912\n\n  TABLE defaultdb.tenant_b.table_d:\n    gc.ttlseconds   = 14400  (4 hours)\n    num_replicas    = 3\n    range_min_bytes = 134217728\n    range_max_bytes = 536870912\n\n## REPLICATION SUMMARY\n\n  Default replication factor : 3 replicas (RANGE default)\n  System/meta/liveness ranges: 5 replicas (elevated for HA)\n  User tables (tenant_b)     : 3 replicas (matches default)\n\n## GC TTL SUMMARY\n\n  Shortest TTL : 600 s  (10 min) — liveness range, lease table,\n                                   replication stats tables\n  Default TTL  : 14400 s (4 h)  — RANGE default, system DB, user tables\n  Longest TTL  : 14400 s (4 h)  — (no ranges configured beyond 4 h)\n\n## NON-DEFAULT TUNING HIGHLIGHTS\n\n  1. kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate = 208 MiB\n     Significantly higher than the 32 MiB default. This accelerates\n     rebalancing after node failures but increases intra-cluster network\n     bandwidth consumption during rebalance events.\n\n  2. kv.range_merge.queue.enabled = false\n     Range auto-merging is disabled. Ranges will not automatically merge\n     when they fall below range_min_bytes. This may result in range\n     fragmentation over time but prevents unexpected merge storms.\n\n  3. diagnostics.reporting.enabled = true\n     Cluster diagnostic telemetry is being sent to Cockroach Labs.\n     Verify this is acceptable per organizational data policies.\n\n  4. system DB / meta / system / liveness ranges use num_replicas = 5\n     These critical internal ranges have elevated replication (5 vs\n     default 3), providing additional fault tolerance for cluster\n     metadata. With a 3-node cluster this means all 3 nodes must hold\n     these replicas (over-replication target; CockroachDB will\n     under-replicate to the available 3 nodes and report a warning).\n\n  5. Custom zones on defaultdb.tenant_b.table_c and table_d\n     These application tables have explicit zone configs with 3 replicas\n     and 4-hour GC TTL, matching the cluster default.\n\n## AUDIT CONCLUSION\n\n  Cluster is healthy (3/3 nodes live). Key non-default settings are:\n  elevated snapshot rebalance rate, disabled range merge queue, and\n  diagnostics reporting enabled. System ranges are configured for\n  5-replica replication (will be capped to 3 on this 3-node cluster).\n  No schema-level configurations deviate from expected compliance\n  baselines beyond the items listed above.\n\n  This audit was performed READ-ONLY. No cluster configuration was modified.\nAUDIT_EOF\necho \"findings.txt written ($(wc -l < /tmp/findings.txt) lines)\"","description":"Write audit findings to a temp file"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":